<event name="RAD_LAB_QUEST_1">
	<text>"Most excellent. To begin with, understand that a lot of this is highly advanced, so try to keep it under wraps."
	Goose walks you over to a terminal on the wall.
	"Our current issue revolves this station design here." The scientist says, gesturing to the strange looking station design on the terminal screen.
	"As you can see, we've equipped this station with a prototype jump drive, allowing us to move it between systems. It's not agile, but it works. Anyway, on a recent test drive, it was captured by pirates. Well... one pirate. And due to our overconfidence in the station defences, we have no way of tracking it down."
	</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Seems bleak. What do you want us to do?</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Ah! Well, luckily we've actually managed to track down the pirates who stole our station. Just the pirates, though. Unfortunately, we don't know where they've put the station."
			The scientist shows you some coordinates on a tablet.
			"What we need is for you to go find them, and attack them. But DON'T KILL THEM, just damage them enough that they try to jump away, and when they do, follow them. We'll give you a device that you can use to follow them when they jump away."
			"Oh, and once you find the station we'll come and meet you with the payment. Good hunting."</text>
			<augment name="RAD_JUMP_TRACKER"/>
			<quest event="RAD_PIRATE_TRACKING_1"/>
			<store>STORE_RADLAB</store>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

